EENG 5301 - Wireless Communications and Networks
Introduction to Wireless Communications and Networks: transmission
fundamentals, LANs, MANs, WANs, switching, ATM, TCP/IP;
Wireless Communications: antennas, propagation, signal encoding,
spread spectrum, error control; Wireless Networking: satellite
communications, cellular networks, analog, TDMA, CDMA, cordless
systems, wireless local loop, mobile IP, WAP; Wireless LANS: infrared,
spread spectrum, microwave, IEEE 802.11, Bluetooth.
Prerequisite: EENG 4312 or consent of the instructor.
